body:
Please forgive my ignorance if it is not a bug.

From javadoc of `com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.annotation.JsonSerialize#converter`

>    Which helper object is to be used to convert type into something
>    that Jackson knows how to serialize; either because base type
>     can not be serialized easily, or just to alter serialization.
> 
>    public Class<? extends Converter<?,?>> converter() default Converter.None.class;

I could not see any restriction regarding types. And basically I want to convert `ConvertingBean` to `DummyBean` but it throws exception.

`````` java
public class TestConvertingSerializer2
   extends com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.BaseMapTest {


   @JsonSerialize(converter = ConvertingBeanConverter2.class)
   static class ConvertingBean { 
      public int x, y; 
      public ConvertingBean(int v1, int v2) {
         x = v1;
         y = v2;
      }
   }

   public static class DummyBean {

      public int a, b;
      public DummyBean(int v1, int v2) {
         a = v1 * 2;
         b = v2 * 2;
      }
   }

   static class ConvertingBeanConverter2 extends StdConverter<ConvertingBean, DummyBean> {

      @Override
      public DummyBean convert(ConvertingBean value) {
         return new DummyBean(31, 333333);
      }
   }

    /*
    /**********************************************************
    /* Test methods
    /**********************************************************
     */


   public void testClassAnnotationSimple() throws Exception {
      // throws exception

      /*
      * com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonMappingException:
      * Can not set int field com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.convert.TestConvertingSerializer2$ConvertingBean.x
      * to com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.convert.TestConvertingSerializer2$DummyBean (through reference chain:
      * com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.convert.DummyBean["x"])
      * */
      String json = objectWriter().writeValueAsString(new ConvertingBean(1, 2));

      // must be  {"a":2,"b":4}
      System.out.println(json);

   }

}```
